contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

07:05.951 --> 07:07.985
(cell phone beeps and dials)

07:07.985 --> 07:10.415
(telephone rings)

07:10.415 --> 07:14.184
Hi. Could you connect me
to dennis york, please?

07:14.184 --> 07:17.109
(doorbell rings)

07:17.109 --> 07:18.783
(groans) who iit?

07:19.528 --> 07:20.504
It's simon.

07:21.535 --> 07:23.585
Uh...

07:23.585 --> 07:25.881
Yes. Um, well,

07:26.181 --> 07:28.102
Just one moment, please.

07:29.116 --> 07:30.282
I'll be right there.

07:30.682 --> 07:31.933
Just...

07:32.233 --> 07:33.809
I'm on my way.

07:44.536 --> 07:46.010
Simon, what are you doing here?

07:46.738 --> 07:49.027
I wasn't sure if you were
checking your phone messages.

07:49.027 --> 07:52.070
No, I've been checking them.
I-I've just been very busy.

07:52.070 --> 07:53.769
I'm sorry if I'm interrupting.

07:54.866 --> 07:57.188
I... Thought maybe
if I tried my luck in person,

07:57.188 --> 07:58.699
You'd give me
the chance to explain.

08:00.142 --> 08:03.035
Uh, that was a bad idea.
I'll go.

08:03.035 --> 08:05.909
No, simon. We should talk.

08:05.909 --> 08:08.079
Please come in. We'll talk.

08:16.277 --> 08:17.597
Sync by ReHelen

08:17.597 --> 08:19.651
www.addic7ed.com

08:20.534 --> 08:21.209
Okay.

08:21.209 --> 08:22.079
(electricity crackles)

08:26.044 --> 08:26.761
And?

08:26.761 --> 08:29.370
That's it. The light goes on.

08:29.370 --> 08:33.076
Oh, wow. I--that--that--that--
That's awesome, isn't it, kevin?

08:33.969 --> 08:35.746
Well, yeah, yeah.
Yeah, it's awesome.

08:35.746 --> 08:38.494
It's jt--you know what? It's a little hard to see.
Really?

08:38.494 --> 08:38.962
I-I saw it. It's fin

08:38.962 --> 08:41.076
yeah, no, I saw it, too.
I just think--you know what?

08:41.076 --> 08:44.629
<i>I think we could--we could amp
this up. Get it? Amp it up?
(snaps fingers)</i>

08:44.629 --> 08:45.630
I know what a pun is,

08:45.630 --> 08:47.480
<i>I just really didn't get
a charge out of it.</i>

08:47.480 --> 08:49.176
I like you, paige whedon.

08:49.176 --> 08:52.390
(chuckles) so what should we do
to see it better?

08:52.390 --> 08:53.767
Nothing.
The project is perfect.

08:53.767 --> 08:57.446
W--yeah. Yes, it is perfect.
But you know what?

08:57.446 --> 09:00.575
When I walk into a courtroom,
I think of two things, okay?
(groans)

09:00.575 --> 09:03.503
Facts and presentation.
The fact is, the battery works.

09:03.503 --> 09:04.218
Great.

09:04.218 --> 09:08.571
If we could build a bigger battery
And turn on something bigger,

09:08.571 --> 09:10.829
I think we would really wow
the judges.

09:10.829 --> 09:11.549
Like a radio.

09:11.549 --> 09:14.317
Yeah, radio's a good start.
Okay, I'm off to aunt kitty's.

09:14.317 --> 09:16.584
Mom, do we have a radio?
A radio? Why?

09:16.584 --> 09:17.820
Do we have one or not?

09:18.958 --> 09:21.752
Uh, yes. Yes, I think there is
one in the attic.

09:21.752 --> 09:22.527
I'll get it.

09:26.200 --> 09:27.182
(lowered voice) thank you.

09:27.555 --> 09:29.459
She won't let me
near this project.

09:29.459 --> 09:31.141
What can I say?
I think I've got the touch.

09:31.141 --> 09:33.032
(normal voice) have you
ever argued with a tween?

09:33.487 --> 09:35.089
I have. I-I live with him.

09:35.089 --> 09:38.683
-Says the miley fan.
-It's good practice for you two.

09:38.683 --> 09:40.486
-Right?
-Okay, I'm off. I'm off!

09:40.486 --> 09:41.763
-Bye.
-Bye.

09:44.431 --> 09:46.683
You know, if you're not in the mood,
We don't have to do this.

09:46.683 --> 09:48.509
Yeah. No, why--why--why wouldn't
I be in the mood?

09:49.477 --> 09:50.165
No reason.

09:51.810 --> 09:54.039
Okay. Just because you're
feeling full of yourself

09:54.039 --> 09:56.075
Because you have
five healthy embryos...

09:55.863 --> 09:56.863
What are you talking about?

09:56.864 --> 10:00.859
-It doesn't mean that I'm not happy with my three.
-And you should be. Three's great.

10:00.859 --> 10:03.774
Ohmy god. If you could hear yourself right now.
What?

10:04.238 --> 10:05.629
-Kevin, it's not--
-I found one.

10:05.629 --> 10:07.964
Okay. Great.

10:09.624 --> 10:11.362
That's what they call it?
Really?

10:11.362 --> 10:14.252
Bone--bone-break fever? That's its name?
Yes, and for good reason.

10:14.252 --> 10:16.321
I felt like my entire body
was in a vise.

10:17.011 --> 10:18.217
By the time I got over it,

10:18.647 --> 10:21.185
I figured it would be best
to explain it to you in person,

10:21.804 --> 10:24.063
And that was a-a bad call.

10:25.570 --> 10:28.215
Oh, just--wait a second.
Just go--go back.

10:28.215 --> 10:30.139
What--what--what happened now

10:30.139 --> 10:32.132
With the community bank
you started?

10:32.132 --> 10:33.925
Well, as soon as I found out
this guy carlsson

10:33.925 --> 10:38.050
-Was stealing from me, I flew straight to guatemala.
-I thought you flew straight to florida.

10:38.050 --> 10:39.809
No, that was a-that was a layover.

10:39.809 --> 10:42.045
But as it turned out,
the president of the bank

10:42.045 --> 10:44.455
Was also on to him,
so when I got to guatemala city,

10:44.455 --> 10:46.416
We just turned him over to 
the authorities.

10:46.416 --> 10:48.320
And then that's when you went
into the jungle?

10:48.320 --> 10:50.194
Uh, right. I wanted
to check on my projects.

10:50.194 --> 10:51.467
They were all up and running,

10:51.467 --> 10:53.038
And everything would have
been great

10:53.038 --> 10:58.187
If it hadn't been for that one
mosquito bite, and... (laughs)

10:58.187 --> 11:00.804
I'm--you don't believe a word
I'm saying, do you? I...

11:00.804 --> 11:03.498
No, I-I do. I do. I-I do.

11:03.498 --> 11:05.697
-I believe you.
-Nora, do you know what worried me the most?

11:05.897 --> 11:08.956
Is that you would think
that's what I would do to you,

11:08.956 --> 11:12.077
-Try and take your money.
-No. I...

11:13.639 --> 11:16.083
Well, I, you know,
I have to be honest,

11:16.083 --> 11:18.157
I've been confused.

11:18.157 --> 11:19.774
I-I've been worried.

11:19.774 --> 11:22.114
-And...
-Nora.

11:22.114 --> 11:23.696
I don't know. I started
to think it was all a dream--

11:23.696 --> 11:26.910
-Whatever we were.
-I'm sorry I put you through this,

11:26.910 --> 11:29.660
Especially when kitty's going
through something much worse.

11:31.334 --> 11:32.890
I wish I could have been here
to help.

11:33.937 --> 11:36.574
Well, she's in remission now,
and that's all that counts.

11:36.574 --> 11:37.300
Mm-hmm.

11:43.265 --> 11:45.496
I know we can't pick up
right where we left off.

11:45.512 --> 11:46.266
I know that.

11:48.057 --> 11:49.635
But can I least see you again?

11:52.385 --> 11:53.596
Well, I-I'm just...

11:54.864 --> 11:56.019
I just need some time.

11:56.019 --> 11:57.875
-I understand.
-Okay.

11:58.399 --> 11:59.156
I'll wait.

12:00.397 --> 12:01.190
I'm persistent.

12:01.190 --> 12:02.426
I'll wait.

12:03.597 --> 12:04.202
Okay.

12:05.115 --> 12:06.734
So finally in a mood to sell?

12:07.924 --> 12:10.727
We'll see. We haven't started
negotiating yet.

12:10.727 --> 12:12.799
Holly, my offer is
more than fair.

12:13.362 --> 12:16.507
Yeah, if I were only selling
a couple of shares.

12:16.507 --> 12:20.741
But you would have a major say
in how this company was run,

12:20.741 --> 12:22.868
So that has to be figured
into the price as well.

12:22.868 --> 12:25.594
It is. 250 is already over value.

12:27.924 --> 12:29.233
(indistinct conversations)

12:29.791 --> 12:32.137
0 a share.

12:32.137 --> 12:32.846
(laughs)

12:33.418 --> 12:34.381
That's...

12:35.418 --> 12:36.350
You're kidding, right?

12:36.350 --> 12:38.444
(chuckles)
everyone has a price.

12:39.226 --> 12:40.110
That's mine.

12:40.110 --> 12:41.629
400? That's crazy.

12:41.629 --> 12:42.727
See, I don't think so.

12:44.108 --> 12:46.457
I mean, correct me if I'm wrong,

12:46.457 --> 12:49.825
But you have been waiting
for this opportunity

12:49.825 --> 12:51.538
Your whole life.

12:51.538 --> 12:54.637
Ojai foods was yours,
not william walker's.

12:54.637 --> 12:56.700
Isn't that the way
that you see it?

12:57.331 --> 13:00.069
But he landed you in jail

13:00.069 --> 13:02.465
And he took the whole thing
for himself.

13:02.465 --> 13:06.485
So I am offering you a chance
to get it back

13:06.485 --> 13:09.402
And to wield power
over his entire family.

13:11.198 --> 13:14.819
Now, dennis, if revenge
is what you're after,

13:15.653 --> 13:18.562
Then $400 is a steal.

13:20.838 --> 13:21.686
Pfft.

13:22.317 --> 13:23.885
You're really persuasive.

13:26.229 --> 13:27.793
350, and that's final.

13:30.531 --> 13:32.054
That's an offer worth considering.

13:32.895 --> 13:34.550
I'll think about it.

13:34.550 --> 13:36.233
48 hours, and it's off the table.

13:36.920 --> 13:37.862
Understood.

13:39.215 --> 13:40.634
Holly.
Hmm?

13:40.634 --> 13:43.753
Just out of curiosity,
when we last spoke, um,

13:43.953 --> 13:46.765
You had no interest in selling.
What changed your mind?

13:48.673 --> 13:52.094
The walkers come with
a whole lot of family drama.

13:53.170 --> 13:55.509
I'm getting real tired of it.

13:56.055 --> 13:57.313
See you, dennis.

14:02.116 --> 14:03.367
Hey.
Hey.

14:04.023 --> 14:04.835
What do you got there?

14:05.605 --> 14:08.061
Well, my o.B. Says that I need
more calcium in my diet,

14:08.061 --> 14:09.442
And since I hate milk--

14:09.755 --> 14:12.977
Chocolate, chocolate chip,
chocolate chip cookie dough.

14:13.077 --> 14:15.428
Tting a jump
on the next semester?

14:15.428 --> 14:18.638
No. I'm getting a jump
on electrons and electrodes.

14:18.638 --> 14:20.924
Sarah asked me and kev to help
paige with her science project.

14:20.924 --> 14:22.008
You have time for that?

14:22.008 --> 14:23.690
Are you implying
I don't have time for that?

14:23.690 --> 14:24.511
Honest answer?

14:24.511 --> 14:26.444
I'm a little surprised
that you're helping paige

14:26.444 --> 14:28.604
When your advisor gave you
a reading list a mile long.

14:28.604 --> 14:30.144
I mean, does sarah even know
what's going on?

14:30.144 --> 14:31.966
Does she know I'm failing
out of medical school? No.

14:31.966 --> 14:34.588
-And she's not gonna find out.
-I'm sure she'd understand.

14:34.588 --> 14:36.318
There's nothing to understand.
I don't even understand.

14:36.318 --> 14:37.251
I studied for these exams.

14:37.251 --> 14:39.083
Did you tell them about kitty
or, I don't know,

14:39.083 --> 14:40.553
That you just found out that
you're gonna be a new father?

14:40.553 --> 14:42.540
Yeah, I did. And you know
what i sounds like?

14:42.540 --> 14:43.827
It sounds like
"my dog ate my homework."

14:47.275 --> 14:48.447
He thinks I should drop out.
Poon clatters)

14:48.447 --> 14:52.631
How cod he say that? He's your advisor.
Yeah, well, that was his advice.

14:52.631 --> 14:55.363
Well, that's ridiculous. You'r.
Okay, rebecca, you know what?

14:55.363 --> 14:56.761
I don't need
the encouraging thing right now.

14:56.761 --> 14:58.465
I'm past needing a cheerleader.
Maybe he's right.

14:58.465 --> 15:01.017
You know, maybe I don't have
what it takes to finish.

15:01.017 --> 15:02.611
I'm sure that everyone
inour class thinks that--

15:02.611 --> 15:05.549
But they're not on probation.
I don't know. All right?

15:05.549 --> 15:06.798
I'm not making a decision
right now.

15:06.798 --> 15:08.443
Where are you going?
We need to talk about this.

15:08.443 --> 15:09.616
Look, I can't think about this,
all right? I'm late.

15:12.251 --> 15:13.148
(door closes)

15:16.783 --> 15:20.105
1.23 watts.
Okay, more lemons, doctor, stat.

15:20.105 --> 15:22.520
Stop calling me "doctor."
and why did we pay for these?

15:22.520 --> 15:23.433
We own a fruit company.

15:23.433 --> 15:25.263
Well, desperate times call
for desperate measures.

15:25.264 --> 15:26.865
Okay, how are we doing
on this display?

15:26.865 --> 15:30.463
We are still glittering.
My father would be so proud.

15:30.463 --> 15:31.841
Great. Make sure
you get the corner

15:31.841 --> 15:34.176
Right. I don't know why I'm so worried
about being a dad.

15:34.176 --> 15:35.514
I think I was born to do this.

15:35.514 --> 15:37.168
(justin)
whoa. Look at this thing.

15:37.544 --> 15:39.198
Remember when we used to
steal this out of sarah's room

15:39.198 --> 15:41.468
And take it to the beach?
Yeah, can we forget
the "back in the day" speech

15:41.468 --> 15:43.298
And concentrate
on the dancing hamster?

15:44.594 --> 15:48.032
Uh, no dancing hamster.
What do you mean, no dan--

15:48.032 --> 15:50.030
How can they be
out of dancing hamsters?

15:50.030 --> 15:53.059
-That's the key to our success.
-A dancing rodent is the key?

15:53.059 --> 15:54.751
Yeah, make the judges laugh--
that's basic.

15:54.751 --> 15:58.024
-Did you check aisle seven?
-I did, and that's what I got.

15:58.058 --> 16:00.254
Of course you picked a robot.
How butch.

16:00.254 --> 16:01.549
Wait. How is a robot butch?

16:02.325 --> 16:04.297
Why don't you turn it on?
(whirring)

16:04.888 --> 16:06.945
-Yeah!
-(paige) awesome.

16:08.323 --> 16:09.796
Okay, that's pretty butch.

16:09.796 --> 16:12.267
See, a science project is about science.
I beg to differ.

16:12.267 --> 16:15.528
Paige, don't let anyone tell you
winning doesn't matter. It does.

16:20.308 --> 16:21.727
Aren't you gonna
tell me, "no, it doesn't"?

16:21.727 --> 16:23.222
If you can't do it,
you can't do it. Right?

16:23.222 --> 16:24.030
<i>That's the way the world works.</i>

16:24.872 --> 16:27.512
Wow. Medical school is
teaching you something.

16:27.512 --> 16:28.585
You have no idea.

16:28.585 --> 16:30.317
You know, I think what
your uncles are trying to say

16:30.317 --> 16:32.335
Is that it's learning
that's important.

16:32.735 --> 16:33.320
Uh-huh.

16:34.207 --> 16:37.195
So what about the disco balls?
Are we still using them?

16:37.395 --> 16:38.999
Absolutely.

16:39.980 --> 16:42.970
Our brother kevin,
who did the baking soda volcano

16:42.970 --> 16:45.689
-Six years in a row?
-Dressed as a wizard, don't forget.

16:45.689 --> 16:47.117
-And justin's there, too.
-Mm-hmm.

16:47.117 --> 16:49.591
Well, oh, oh, well, now that's
a good idea. You know, justin--

16:49.591 --> 16:51.972
Justin who just didn't do his
science projects altogether.

16:51.972 --> 16:54.055
Well, considering how much
I helped him at school,

16:54.055 --> 16:56.447
He owes me big-time.
But I'm just glad that paige

16:56.447 --> 16:59.038
Accepts their help, because god
knows, she does not want mine.

16:59.038 --> 16:59.746
Sweetheart,
are you all right?

16:59.746 --> 17:01.369
I'm fine.
I just always keep checking

17:01.369 --> 17:02.557
To see if it's swelling.

17:04.559 --> 17:06.565
You're feeling better,
though, right?

17:06.565 --> 17:08.227
I am.
It's just a very bad habit.

17:08.227 --> 17:11.377
As a matter of fact, I spoke
with dr. Avadon yesterday,

17:11.377 --> 17:14.089
Who told me that my white blood
cell count--higher than ever.

17:14.089 --> 17:15.387
Yay! Yay!

17:15.387 --> 17:16.472
Yeah.
Unbelievable, kitty.

17:17.079 --> 17:19.311
How is it having robert home?

17:19.311 --> 17:20.972
Oh, well, it's, um,

17:20.972 --> 17:23.473
You know, it's really,
really nice for me.

17:23.473 --> 17:26.609
-I--he says he's happy.
-But you don't think he is happy?

17:26.609 --> 17:28.030
I just think he misses
the campaign.

17:28.030 --> 17:30.060
Well, it would be weird
if he didn't miss it.

17:30.060 --> 17:31.870
I mean, it's hard
to say good-bye

17:31.870 --> 17:34.608
-To somethingou deeply and truly love.
-That's true.

17:34.608 --> 17:37.246
But you do it. You do it.
You say, "hasta la vista," baby.

17:37.246 --> 17:39.085
Stop. Stop.

17:39.085 --> 17:40.328
Mom.
Wait. What are we stopping?

17:40.328 --> 17:42.658
You're taking him back.
I haven't. I haven't made any decisions.

17:42.658 --> 17:43.454
Ugh. This is a bad mistake.
Decisions about what?

17:45.193 --> 17:47.292
-Simon's back.
-Oh, my god.

17:47.292 --> 17:48.835
-Mm-hmm.
-Oh, my god. You're kidding me.

17:48.835 --> 17:53.789
He had the nerve to show his face?
Mnh-mnh. That would require bravery. He just called.

17:53.789 --> 17:57.913
He came to the house, actually.
What? You saidyou weren't gonna see him.

17:57.913 --> 18:01.229
He showed up on my doorstep,
begging me to just hear him out.

18:01.229 --> 18:03.030
Sarah, just because
I hear what he has to say

18:03.030 --> 18:06.000
Does not make me the village idiot.
No, but believing him does.

18:06.000 --> 18:07.439
-Oh, she didn't mean that.
-Yes, she did.

18:07.439 --> 18:10.628
Yes, I did. Yes, I did.
I did, very much. 100%.

18:10.491 --> 18:12.833
-But she meant it out of love and concern.
-I can totally, totally tell you did.

18:12.833 --> 18:16.483
Yes, I'm very protective.
You're too forgiving, mom.

18:16.483 --> 18:18.405
I'm an adult. I can take care
of my own affairs.

18:18.405 --> 18:21.893
-Well, I'm not gonna stop worrying abo you.
-Look, you know, sarah,

18:21.893 --> 18:24.172
I think that in this case, mom is right. I mean, th--
what?

18:24.172 --> 18:26.401
Well, we're always bitching
that she butts into our lives.

18:26.401 --> 18:29.091
So let's just stop butting into hers.
Thank you...

18:30.895 --> 18:31.859
I think.

18:31.859 --> 18:34.285
How about now?

18:35.700 --> 18:36.204
Nope.

18:36.204 --> 18:38.726
What do you mean, "nope"?
I mean we don't have enough volts.

18:39.284 --> 18:41.183
Unless you don't understand
the basic concept

18:42.446 --> 18:45.241
Do you want to help me
make something in the kitchen?

18:45.726 --> 18:47.201
Can I, uncle kevin?

18:47.201 --> 18:49.398
Absolutely, as long
as it doesn't involve fruit.

18:50.061 --> 18:53.716
Are we really out of lemons?
Look, paige said the radio was fine.

18:53.716 --> 18:55.367
-That's not enough.
-It's enough for her.

18:55.367 --> 18:57.790
Look, this is gonna work, okay,
so don't give up so easily.

18:57.790 --> 19:00.265
You know what?
Fine. Jeez. You do it.

19:02.102 --> 19:02.956
What are you doing?

19:02.956 --> 19:05.898
Look, I'm done. You obviously
know what it takes to succeed,

19:05.898 --> 19:07.783
So just--you finish it.

19:10.129 --> 19:11.536
All right, what's going on with you?

19:11.536 --> 19:13.020
I can't watch you take over
paige's project.

19:13.529 --> 19:15.471
I mean, do--do you honestly
think it helps her?

19:15.471 --> 19:19.077
Because it doesn't, kevin.
So what if she wins now?

19:19.077 --> 19:20.306
All right, someday
she'll be in a place

19:20.306 --> 19:21.925
Where no one can help her
and it's all on her.

19:21.925 --> 19:24.872
-And then what?
-Justin, she's in sixth grade.

19:24.872 --> 19:27.309
Yeah, and so was I. And I might
have learned something

19:27.309 --> 19:28.590
If you and everybody else
in this family

19:28.590 --> 19:29.704
Didn't do everything for me.

19:29.704 --> 19:32.212
I'm sorry. What are you talking
about? You're in medical school.

19:32.213 --> 19:33.405
Yeah, and I'm failing out.

19:37.277 --> 19:40.013
-What?
-I'm on academic probation,

19:40.013 --> 19:41.390
And they're trying
to kick me out.

19:42.409 --> 19:43.732
Oh, god.

19:46.637 --> 19:48.431
All right. Um...

19:49.707 --> 19:50.405
Does mom know?

19:50.405 --> 19:53.053
Kevin, I'm a grown man. They
don't send report cards home.

19:53.954 --> 19:55.774
But it doesn't matter,
because I'm gonna drop out.

19:56.747 --> 19:59.960
Look, I gotta go.

19:59.960 --> 20:01.962
Please tell paige
everything's okay,

20:01.962 --> 20:03.301
And I'll see her
at the science fair.

20:11.839 --> 20:14.741
(indistinct conversations)

20:33.895 --> 20:37.230
(keypad beeping)

20:37.265 --> 20:39.099
(beep)

20:39.133 --> 20:41.201
(phone rings)

20:41.235 --> 20:42.084
(ring)

20:43.549 --> 20:44.255
Sarah, where are you?

20:44.255 --> 20:46.735
Paige wanted some space.
Why? Is everything okay?

20:46.735 --> 20:48.293
No, it is not. It's a disaster.

20:48.294 --> 20:50.299
Henry's earthquake simulator
is out-of-control.

20:50.299 --> 20:52.372
-And there is no way he made any of it.
-You don't know that.

20:52.372 --> 20:54.607
-Yes, I do. Where are you?
-I'm about to leave.

20:54.607 --> 20:58.363
-But listen, I found out this thing about simon.
-Simon? Who is si--what, mom's simon?

20:58.363 --> 20:59.317
I googled him again.

20:59.317 --> 21:03.301
There's this picture of him from
some boca raton society page.

21:03.301 --> 21:06.557
He's at a benefit with an older,
attractive woman on his arm--

21:07.020 --> 21:09.519
Marilyn weisman.
Maybe he has a thing for older women.

21:09.519 --> 21:12.340
No. But what if he has one
in every city?

21:12.340 --> 21:14.847
-Don't you think I should tell mom?
-No, I think you should forget about simon

21:14.847 --> 21:16.348
-And start thinking about henry.
-Don't you mean paige?

21:16.348 --> 21:19.118
No. I mean, yeah. J--look, just get down here.
(beep)

21:19.118 --> 21:19.966
(beep)
cooper.

21:19.966 --> 21:21.852
(all talking at once)

21:25.508 --> 21:27.576
Wow, paige. I gotta say,
it looks fantastic.

21:27.576 --> 21:30.757
-(rebecca) yeah, really.
-Do you think it's better han henry's?

21:30.757 --> 21:32.492
-Oh, yeah.
-Who's henry? Your nemesis?

21:32.492 --> 21:36.214
It's more like kevin's nemesis.
(cell phone ringing)

21:36.214 --> 21:39.325
(beep) hi. Could you wait one second
for me?

21:39.325 --> 21:41.557
-Have you seen kevin?
-Uh, yeah, I saw him just a second ago.

21:41.557 --> 21:42.919
-You want me to find him?
-Yeah. Tell him it's important.

21:42.919 --> 21:44.885
-Okay.
-Yes, uh, doctor, go ahead.

21:44.885 --> 21:47.713
Just need to make
a few little tweaks here.

21:51.826 --> 21:52.713
Hi.

21:53.705 --> 21:55.022
Interested in earthquakes?
(chuckles)

21:55.022 --> 21:57.306
I'm sure henry can answer
any of your questions.

21:57.306 --> 22:01.029
Actually, yeah, I do have
a couple of questions, henry.
(mouths word)

22:01.029 --> 22:04.361
Paige, look at that!
It's gigantic.

22:04.361 --> 22:06.633
(gasps) oh, my gosh.

22:06.633 --> 22:08.642
I can't believe
you did all of this.

22:08.642 --> 22:10.866
Well, uncle kevin thought of it

22:10.866 --> 22:12.975
And uncle justin did
the battery work.

22:12.975 --> 22:17.559
-Wait till you see the robot start dancing.
-Is he gonna dance?

22:17.559 --> 22:19.119
That's what the disco balls are for.

22:19.119 --> 22:22.576
Oh, yes, of course.
Well, that's obvious.

22:22.576 --> 22:24.568
Terrific work, justin.

22:24.568 --> 22:26.906
Now you see, paige, if you keep
working on your science,

22:26.906 --> 22:30.711
-Maybe one day you, too, will end up in med school.
-I want to be fashion designer.

22:30.711 --> 22:32.987
-Uh, you know, I'm gonna, uh...
-Well, yes, that's good, too.

22:32.987 --> 22:35.333
-I'm gonna go, uh, go find, uh, rebecca.
-Are you okay?

22:35.333 --> 22:36.844
(justi) yes. Paige's moment.
Paige's moment.

22:38.995 --> 22:41.530
Okay, so what--what does--
what does he dance to?

22:41.530 --> 22:44.353
-Disco.
-Don't tell me that was kevin's idea.

22:44.353 --> 22:46.293
Right,nd you figured
this equation out yourself?

22:46.293 --> 22:48.973
It wasn't hard.
My manipulated variable is

22:48.973 --> 22:50.506
The building's
construction material.

22:50.506 --> 22:52.426
My responding variable is
how long it takes

22:52.426 --> 22:53.103
For the building to collapse.

22:53.103 --> 22:55.343
Right. And how long did it take
to build the model?

22:55.343 --> 22:55.946
A couple days.

22:55.946 --> 22:58.217
A couple of days? What's your
superpower, architecture?

22:58.820 --> 23:00.685
(lowered voice) seriously,
one dad to another,

23:00.685 --> 23:03.858
You, um, you built most of this
yourself, right?

23:04.831 --> 23:06.571
I'm sorry.
Whose father are you?

23:08.137 --> 23:09.129
That's not relevant.

23:09.129 --> 23:10.557
-What's your name?
-Sterling.

23:10.557 --> 23:13.093
(scotty) kevin. Sterling kevin. Good luck.

23:13.093 --> 23:14.341
What are you doing?

23:14.341 --> 23:16.608
-I practically had him disqualified.
-I talked to the clinic.

23:16.608 --> 23:19.281
-What? Really? And?
-Yeah. Well, it's not great.

23:19.281 --> 23:21.205
Only four of ours made it
to advanced blasts.

23:21.205 --> 23:23.451
(gasps) you're kidding.

23:23.451 --> 23:25.808
I'm trying to not get depressed.
I mean, we still have four.

23:25.808 --> 23:27.026
-Of course. Of course.
-Yeah.

23:27.026 --> 23:29.364
No, you're absolutely right.
Our baby's our baby.

23:29.364 --> 23:32.693
Did... Any of yours make it?

23:32.693 --> 23:35.537
Oh. No, actually,

23:35.537 --> 23:38.087
<i>The--the four
that didn't make it are yours.</i>

23:38.087 --> 23:39.380
Mine are all good.

23:39.380 --> 23:41.502
I lost four?

23:41.502 --> 23:43.143
The doctor said
there's no rhyme or reason.

23:43.143 --> 23:45.183
I mean, y-your embryo
could end up becoming the one.

23:47.497 --> 23:49.948
-Are you okay? Because I know that--
-I'm fine. I'm fine.

23:49.948 --> 23:52.875
Look, I knew we didn't have
any control over this.

23:52.875 --> 23:56.570
-So I should...I should get back to paige.
-Do you want to talk about this?

23:56.570 --> 23:57.848
No, no, I don't. I'm fine.

23:58.472 --> 24:00.633
Oh, wow, paige.

24:00.633 --> 24:04.029
Didn't this turn out great?
I love it!

24:04.029 --> 24:05.333
It's so bright,

24:05.333 --> 24:08.107
And the information is
very well laid out.

24:08.107 --> 24:10.412
-Coop, what do you think?
-Can I g?

24:10.412 --> 24:12.981
Yeah, sure. Don't stick your
finger in it, though, okay?

24:12.981 --> 24:14.020
What took you so long?

24:14.020 --> 24:16.453
Uh, well, I-I got the impression

24:16.453 --> 24:18.193
That you kinda wanted some space.

24:18.193 --> 24:21.369
-Whatever.
-Wow. I really can't win with you these days.

24:22.022 --> 24:23.436
Um, where's grandma?
Is she here?

24:23.436 --> 24:24.868
She went to look at some booths.

24:24.868 --> 24:26.625
Why don't you go
and look at some, too?

24:28.606 --> 24:30.674
Yeah, why don't I?

24:32.104 --> 24:33.287
(whispers) psst!
Is she gone?

24:33.287 --> 24:35.750
-Yeah.
-(normal voice) okay, huddle up.

24:35.750 --> 24:37.024
I've been doing
some reconnaissance.

24:37.024 --> 24:39.530
-Reconnaissance?
-Sizing up the competition.

24:39.530 --> 24:42.997
Seriously lame, but you're right
about that henry kid, so I think

24:42.997 --> 24:45.149
We pump up the volume,
squeeze in a few more oranges.

24:45.149 --> 24:47.559
-Do we have enough time?
-Yeah, but we gotta get going.

24:50.165 --> 24:52.736
-(sighs) mom, there you are.
-Sarah. Sarah, look.

24:52.736 --> 24:53.739
No, listen--
th-this young--

24:53.739 --> 24:55.105
This young woman
has--has found out

24:55.105 --> 24:57.763
That it's better to water plants
with water than with soda.

24:57.763 --> 25:00.283
That's a stunning finding.

25:00.283 --> 25:03.290
-Mom, could I talk to you, please? Listen.
-Yes.

25:03.290 --> 25:05.654
I know simon gave you
an explanation,

25:05.654 --> 25:09.773
-But I found something out about him.
-(sighs) sarah, what part
of "I can handle it"

25:09.773 --> 25:14.316
-Don't you understand, huh?
-Listen, I was just--I was
looking around online and--

25:14.316 --> 25:15.676
What, are you spying on him again?

25:15.676 --> 25:18.096
Well, googling is not spying.

25:18.096 --> 25:19.486
It's social networking.

25:19.486 --> 25:22.227
Anyway, listen, I know
that you're fond of him,

25:22.227 --> 25:26.437
-But I found something out about him--
-There is nothing about simon
that I don't already know.

25:26.727 --> 25:29.223
God, what--what is this guy's
power over you?

25:29.223 --> 25:32.145
My god, now you're insulting me.
He has no power over me.
(cell phone ringing)

25:32.145 --> 25:34.344
